 Difining bash scripting: A bash cript a container that host linux commands and authomates them as the script run.
 Knowing variables and substitutions in bash
   A variable is a named container that stores a value (text or numbers) that can change while the script executes.
   Declaring a variable
   name="Chester"
   count=10
 Substitution means replacing something with its value or result.
 Making conditional statements in a bash scripts
if [ "$age" -ge 18 ]; then
  echo "You are an adult"
elif [ "$age" -ge 13 ]; then
  echo "You are a teenager"
else
  echo "You are a child"
fi
